locality: Yemen: Gov. Al-Mahra. Jabal Sharwayn 10 km W of Qeshn, rocky slopes and plateau looking on the Qeshn plain. Rocky slopes, strongly affected by the monsoonal mist: succulent rich Euphorbia balsamifera zone. Alt.: 180 m. 24.9.1998, Leg.: P. Hein, S. A. Ghazanfar & N. Kilian PH 4892.

Yemen: Gov. Al-Mahra. Northern Fartak Mts, dissected table-land near the track W below J. Karmoum (with the disused radio tower). Relevé A31: Steep rocky NNE-exp. slope (incl. 15-20°) with small rock steps and stones between. Vegetation dominated by dwarf shrubs. Alt.: 600-650 m. 8.10.2001, Leg.: P. Hein, H. Kürschner & M. Reisch YP 1106.
